CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Get_GetCalculateWorkingDayPeriodByIsDefault]
    @DbName VARCHAR(500)
AS
    BEGIN
        DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
            @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
        SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_' + @DbName + ']'
            + N'
						SELECT  DWP.AutoId ,
						DWP.Name ,
						DWP.FromDay,
						DWP.Today,
						DWP.MaximumEdition ,
						DWP.IsDefault ,
						DWP.Note ,
						DWP.Status ,
						DWS.WorkId
						FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period DWP
						LEFT JOIN dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift DWS on DWS.PeriodId=DWP.AutoId
						WHERE DWP.IsDefault=1								
					'
        SET @params = ''
        EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params

    END
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Get_GetPeriod]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
 

/*
***************************************************************************
	-- Author:			nhungpt
	-- Description:		Update User
	-- Date				21/11/2019					Update record
***************************************************************************
*/
CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Get_GetPeriod]
    @BaseParam BaseParamType READONLY ,
    @TotalRecord INT = 0 OUTPUT
AS --begin try
    DECLARE @FilterField NVARCHAR(MAX) = '' ,
        @OrderBy VARCHAR(100) = '' ,
        @PageNumber INT = 1 ,
        @PageSize INT = 9000000 ,
        @UserId INT = 1 ,
        @RoleId INT = 1 ,
        @DBName NVARCHAR(50) = 'Hrm_System' ,
        @LanguageId INT = 1
    IF EXISTS ( SELECT TOP 1
                        *
                FROM    @BaseParam )
        BEGIN
            SELECT TOP 1
                    @FilterField = FilterField ,
                    @OrderBy = OrderBy ,
                    @PageNumber = PageNumber ,
                    @PageSize = PageSize ,
                    @UserId = UserId ,
                    @RoleId = RoleId ,
                    @DBName = DbName ,
                    @LanguageId = LanguageId
            FROM    @BaseParam
        END
    DECLARE @WhereSQL NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @Delim NVARCHAR(100) ,
        @StartIndex BIGINT ,
        @EndIndex BIGINT ,
        @SQL NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @SQLCount NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @SQLFrom NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @SQLSelect NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @dynamicsql NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @dynamicparamdec NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @SearchResult BIGINT ,
        @OrderBySQL VARCHAR(MAX) ,
        @WhereSQLRight NVARCHAR(MAX)

    SET @OrderBy = ISNULL(@OrderBy, ' DWS.Id desc')
    SET @FilterField = ISNULL(@FilterField, '')
    SET @WhereSQL = ' ' 
    SET @WhereSQLRight = ''
    SET @PageNumber = CASE WHEN ISNULL(@PageNumber, 0) = 0 THEN 1
                           ELSE CONVERT(INT, @PageNumber)
                      END
    SET @PageSize = CASE WHEN ISNULL(@PageSize, 0) = 0 THEN 50
                         ELSE CONVERT(INT, @PageSize)
                    END

		--1. Calculate to paging
    SET @StartIndex = @PageSize * @PageNumber
    SET @EndIndex = @StartIndex + @PageSize

    SET @StartIndex = ( ( @PageNumber - 1 ) * @PageSize ) + 1
    SET @EndIndex = @PageNumber * @PageSize

    IF @FilterField <> ''
        BEGIN
            SET @Delim = ' '
            SET @WhereSQL = @WhereSQL + @Delim + @FilterField
        END
		--2. get right for role or user

		-- set @WhereSQLRight by role or user

    IF @WhereSQLRight <> ''
        BEGIN
            SET @Delim = ' '
            SET @WhereSQL = @WhereSQL + @Delim + @WhereSQLRight
        END

		--3. Build select query

    SET @SQLSelect = N'USE [Hrm_' + @DBName + ']'
        + N'
					SELECT 
						DWP.AutoId AS Id,
					    DWP.AutoId, DWP.Name,
						DWP.FromDay AS FromDate,
						DWP.Today AS ToDate,
						DWP.MaximumEdition,
						DWP.Note,	
						DWP.Status											
			'				
    SET @SQLFrom = ' FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Period DWP'

    SET @SQL = @SQLSelect + @SQLFrom + ' WHERE DWP.IsDeleted = 0 ' + @WhereSQL
        + ' ORDER BY DWP.AutoId DESC
		  OFFSET  ' + CONVERT(VARCHAR, ( @PageNumber - 1 ) * @PageSize)
        + ' ROWS  FETCH NEXT ' + CONVERT(VARCHAR, @PageSize) + ' ROWS ONLY '
		  
    EXEC(@SQL )
    PRINT @SQL
		--4. Count
    SET @SQLCount = N'USE [Hrm_' + @DBName + ']'
        + ' SELECT @TotalRecord = COUNT(DWP.AutoId) '
    SET @dynamicsql = @SQLCount + @SQLFrom + '  WHERE DWP.IsDeleted = 0 '
        + @WhereSQL
    SET @dynamicparamdec = '@TotalRecord INT OUTPUT'
    EXECUTE sp_executesql @dynamicsql, @dynamicparamdec, @TotalRecord OUTPUT

	--end try

	--begin catch

	--	declare	@ErrorNum				int,
	--			@ErrorMsg				varchar(200),
	--			@ErrorProc				varchar(50),
	--			@SessionId				int,
	--			@AddlInfo				varchar(max)

	--	set @ErrorNum					= error_number()
	--	set @ErrorMsg					= 'System_Get_GetAllData_Organization: ' + error_message()
	--	set @ErrorProc					= error_procedure()
	--	set @AddlInfo					= '@OrderBy=' + @OrderBy

	--	exec utl_Insert_ErrorLog @ErrorNum,@DbName, @ErrorMsg, @ErrorProc, 'Data_Staff_Information', 'GET', @SessionId, @AddlInfo

	--end catch

GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Get_GetWorkDayByPeroidId]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Get_GetWorkDayByPeroidId]
	@PeriodID BIGINT,
	@DbName NVARCHAR(100)
AS
 
BEGIN	

	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'	
				SELECT  DWW.Id ,
				DWW.PeriodID ,
				DWW.Monday ,
				DWW.Tuesday ,
				DWW.Wednesday ,
				DWW.Thursday ,
				DWW.Friday ,
				DWW.Saturday ,
				DWW.Sunday ,
				DWW.OrderWeek
				FROM    dbo.Data_WorkingDay_WorkDay DWW
				WHERE   DWW.PeriodID = @PeriodID
						AND DWW.IsDeleted = 0 
		'
	SET @params = '@PeriodID BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@PeriodID

END

GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Update_SaveCalculateWorkingDayPeriod]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[WorkingDayCalculationPeriod_Update_SaveCalculateWorkingDayPeriod]
    @Id BIGINT ,
    @Name NVARCHAR(500) ,
    @FromDate INT ,
    @ToDate INT ,
    @Status BIGINT ,
    @Note NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
    @UserID BIGINT ,
    @MaximumEdition INT ,
    @IsDefault BIT ,
    @DbName NVARCHAR(500) ,
    @WorkDayPeriodType WorkDayType READONLY
AS
    BEGIN
        DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
            @params NVARCHAR(MAX)	   				
															 
        SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_' + @DbName + ']'
            + N'
				IF ( @IsDefault = 1 )
    BEGIN
        UPDATE  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period
        SET     IsDefault = 0
    END
IF ( @Id = 0 )
    BEGIN
        INSERT  INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_Period
                ( Name ,
                  FromDay ,
                  Today ,
                  Status ,
                  Note ,
                  IsDeleted ,
                  IsDefault ,
                  MaximumEdition ,
                  CreatedBy ,
                  CreatedDate
			    )
        VALUES  ( @Name , -- Name - NVARCHAR(500)
                  @FromDate , -- FromDate - INT
                  @ToDate , -- ToDate - INT
                  @Status , -- Status - INT
                  @Note , -- Note - NVARCHAR(MAX),							  
                  0 ,  -- IsDeleted - bit							  
                  @IsDefault ,  -- IsDefault - bit
                  @MaximumEdition , -- MaximumEdition INT
                  @UserID , -- UserID - INT
                  GETDATE() -- CreatedDate - DATETIME
						
                )
        SET @Id = SCOPE_IDENTITY()
        IF ( ( SELECT   COUNT(Id)
               FROM     @WorkDayPeriodType
               WHERE    Id = 0
             ) > 0 )
            BEGIN
                INSERT  INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_WorkDay
                        ( 
						  [PeriodID] ,
                          [Monday] ,
                          [Tuesday] ,
                          [Wednesday] ,
                          [Thursday] ,
                          [Friday] ,
                          [Saturday] ,
                          [Sunday] ,
                          [OrderWeek] ,
                          [IsDeleted]
								
                        )
                        SELECT  @Id --WorkingDayPeriodID
                                ,
                                WDPT.Monday ,
                                WDPT.Tuesday ,
                                WDPT.Wednesday ,
                                WDPT.Thursday ,
                                WDPT.Friday ,
                                WDPT.Saturday ,
                                WDPT.Sunday ,
                                WDPT.OrderWeek ,
                                0
                        FROM    @WorkDayPeriodType WDPT
                        WHERE   WDPT.Id = 0
            END
    END
ELSE
    BEGIN
	--update calculate working day period
		UPDATE  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period
		SET     Name = @Name ,
				FromDay = @FromDate ,
				Today = @ToDate ,
				Status = @Status ,
				Note = @Note ,
				IsDefault = @IsDefault ,
				MaximumEdition = @MaximumEdition
		WHERE   AutoId = @Id	
	--update workday	
		UPDATE  DWW
		SET     DWW.Monday = WDPT.Monday
			    ,DWW.Tuesday = WDPT.Tuesday
			    ,DWW.Wednesday = WDPT.Wednesday
				,DWW.Thursday = WDPT.Thursday
				,DWW.Friday = WDPT.Friday
				,DWW.Saturday = WDPT.Saturday
				,DWW.Sunday = WDPT.Sunday
		FROM    dbo.Data_WorkingDay_WorkDay DWW
				INNER JOIN @WorkDayPeriodType WDPT ON DWW.Id = WDPT.Id
	END														
			'
        SET @params = ' @Id BIGINT ,
						@Name NVARCHAR(500) ,
						@FromDate INT ,
						@ToDate INT ,
						@Status BIGINT ,
						@Note NVARCHAR(MAX) ,
						@UserID BIGINT ,
						@MaximumEdition INT ,
						@IsDefault BIT,
						@DbName NVARCHAR(500),
						@WorkDayPeriodType WorkDayType READONLY
						'
        EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params, @Id, @Name, @FromDate, @ToDate,
            @Status, @Note, @UserID, @MaximumEdition, @IsDefault, @DbName,
            @WorkDayPeriodType
	
    END

GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayHoliday_Get_GetWorkingdayHoliday]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
 

/*
***************************************************************************
	-- Author:			nhungpt
	-- Description:		Update User
	-- Date				21/11/2019					Update record
***************************************************************************
*/
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayHoliday_Get_GetWorkingdayHoliday]
	@BaseParam BaseParamType READONLY,	
	@TotalRecord int = 0 output
AS
--begin try
	DECLARE @FilterField		NVARCHAR(MAX) = '',
			@OrderBy			VARCHAR(100) = '',
			@PageNumber			INT = 1,
			@PageSize			INT = 9000000,
			@UserId				INT = 1,
			@RoleId				INT = 1,
			@DBName				NVARCHAR(50) = 'Hrm_System',
			@LanguageId			INT = 1
		IF EXISTS(SELECT TOP 1 * FROM @BaseParam)
		BEGIN
			SELECT TOP 1 @FilterField = FilterField,
						 @OrderBy	  = OrderBy,	
						 @PageNumber  = PageNumber,
						 @PageSize	  = PageSize,
						 @UserId	  = UserId,	
						 @RoleId	  = RoleId,
						 @DbName	  = DbName,	
						 @LanguageId  = LanguageId	
			FROM @BaseParam
		END
		declare	@WhereSQL				nvarchar(max),
				@Delim					nvarchar(100),
				@StartIndex				bigint,
				
				@EndIndex				bigint,
				@SQL					nvarchar(max),
				@SQLCount					nvarchar(max),
				@SQLFrom				nvarchar(max),
				@SQLSelect					nvarchar(max),
				
				@dynamicsql				nvarchar(max),
				@dynamicparamdec		nvarchar(max),
				@SearchResult			bigint,
				@OrderBySQL				varchar(max),
				@WhereSQLRight				nvarchar(max)

		set		@OrderBy				= isnull(@OrderBy,' DWS.Id desc')
		set		@FilterField			= isnull(@FilterField,'')
		set		@WhereSQL				= ' ' 
		set		@WhereSQLRight			=''
		set		@PageNumber				= case when isnull(@PageNumber,0)	= 0 then 1 else convert(int,@PageNumber) end
		set		@PageSize				= case when isnull(@PageSize,0)	= 0 then 50 else convert(int,@PageSize) end

		--1. Calculate to paging
		set		@StartIndex				= @PageSize * @PageNumber
		set		@EndIndex				= @StartIndex + @PageSize

		set		@StartIndex				= ((@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) + 1
		set		@EndIndex				= @PageNumber * @PageSize

		if @FilterField <> ''
			begin
				set	@Delim				= ' '
				set	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @FilterField
			end
		--2. get right for role or user

		-- set @WhereSQLRight by role or user

		if @WhereSQLRight <> ''
			begin
				set	@Delim				= ' '
				set	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @WhereSQLRight
			end

		--3. Build select query

			set	@SQLSelect						= 
			N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
									SELECT 
										DWH.Id,
										DWH.Name,
										DWH.ClassifyId,
										DWH.IsAnnualLeave,
										DWH.SalaryRegimeId,
										DWH.OvertimeRate,
										DWH.Note,
										DWHM.MaxDate,
										DWHM.MinDate,
										CASE 
											WHEN DWH.IsAnnualLeave=0 AND DWHM.MaxDate>DWHM.MinDate THEN (CONVERT(VARCHAR, DWHM.MinDate,103) + '' - '' + CONVERT(VARCHAR,DWHM.MaxDate,103))
											WHEN DWH.IsAnnualLeave=0 AND DWHM.MaxDate=DWHM.MinDate THEN CONVERT(VARCHAR, DWHM.MaxDate,103)
											WHEN DWH.IsAnnualLeave=1 AND DWHM.MaxDate=DWHM.MinDate THEN CAST(DAY(DWHM.MaxDate) AS VARCHAR(2)) + ''/'' + CAST(MONTH(DWHM.MaxDate) AS VARCHAR(2)) 
											WHEN DWH.IsAnnualLeave=1 AND DWHM.MaxDate>DWHM.MinDate THEN (CAST(DAY(DWHM.MinDate) AS VARCHAR(2)) + ''/'' + CAST(MONTH(DWHM.MinDate) AS VARCHAR(2))) + '' - '' + (CAST(DAY(DWHM.MaxDate) AS VARCHAR(2)) + ''/'' + CAST(MONTH(DWHM.MaxDate) AS VARCHAR(2)))
										END AS ApproxDate																			
			'				
	  set @SQLFrom='FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Holiday DWH
								OUTER APPLY( SELECT MAX(Date) AS MaxDate,MIN(Date) AS MinDate FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_HolidayMapper WHERE HolidayId=DWH.Id AND IsDeleted=0 ) DWHM'

	  set @SQL=@SQLSelect + @SQLFrom+ ' WHERE DWH.IsDeleted = 0 ' +@WhereSQL + 
	   ' ORDER BY DWH.Id DESC
		  OFFSET  '+ convert(varchar,(@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) +' ROWS  FETCH NEXT '+ convert(varchar,@PageSize) +' ROWS ONLY '
		  
		  EXEC(@SQL )
		  PRINT @SQL
		--4. Count
		set @SQLCount=N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + ' SELECT @TotalRecord = COUNT(DWH.Id) '
		set @dynamicsql=@SQLCount + @SQLFrom+ '  WHERE DWH.IsDeleted = 0 ' +@WhereSQL
		set @dynamicparamdec = '@TotalRecord INT OUTPUT'
		execute sp_executesql @dynamicsql,@dynamicparamdec,@TotalRecord  OUTPUT

	--end try

	--begin catch

	--	declare	@ErrorNum				int,
	--			@ErrorMsg				varchar(200),
	--			@ErrorProc				varchar(50),
	--			@SessionId				int,
	--			@AddlInfo				varchar(max)

	--	set @ErrorNum					= error_number()
	--	set @ErrorMsg					= 'System_Get_GetAllData_Organization: ' + error_message()
	--	set @ErrorProc					= error_procedure()
	--	set @AddlInfo					= '@OrderBy=' + @OrderBy

	--	exec utl_Insert_ErrorLog @ErrorNum,@DbName, @ErrorMsg, @ErrorProc, 'Data_Staff_Information', 'GET', @SessionId, @AddlInfo

	--end catch
	 
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayHoliday_Get_GetWorkingDayHolidayById]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayHoliday_Get_GetWorkingDayHolidayById]
	@Id					BIGINT,
	@DbName				VARCHAR(500)
as
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
						SELECT 
							DWH.* ,
							DWHM.MaxDate,
							DWHM.MinDate
						FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Holiday DWH
						OUTER APPLY( SELECT MAX(Date) AS MaxDate,MIN(Date) AS MinDate FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_HolidayMapper WHERE HolidayId=DWH.Id AND IsDeleted=0 ) DWHM
						WHERE DWH.Id=@Id AND DWH.IsDeleted=0															
					'
	SET @params = '@Id BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@Id

END
GO

	@HolidayId				BIGINT,
	@DbName				VARCHAR(500)
as
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
						SELECT * FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper WHERE HolidayId=@HolidayId AND IsDeleted=0																
					'
	SET @params = '@HolidayId BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@HolidayId

END

/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayHoliday_Update_SaveWorkingdayHoliday]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayHoliday_Update_SaveWorkingdayHoliday]
	 @Id BIGINT,
     @Name NVARCHAR(500),
     @ClassifyId BIGINT,
     @IsAnnualLeave	BIT,
     @SalaryRegimeId BIGINT,
     @OvertimeRate	FLOAT,
     @Note  NVARCHAR(500),	
     @CreatedBy BIGINT,
     @DbName NVARCHAR(500),
     @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType WorkingdayHolidayMapperType READONLY
AS
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)	   				
															 
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
				IF(@Id=0)
				BEGIN
					INSERT INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_Holiday
			        ( Name ,
			          ClassifyId ,
			          IsAnnualLeave ,
			          SalaryRegimeId ,
			          OvertimeRate ,
			          Note ,
			          CreatedBy ,
			          CreatedDate ,
			          IsDeleted
			        )
					VALUES  ( @Name , -- Name - nvarchar(max)
						  @ClassifyId , -- ClassifyId - bigint
						  @IsAnnualLeave , -- IsAnnualLeave - bit
						  @SalaryRegimeId , -- SalaryRegimeId - bigint
						  @OvertimeRate , -- OvertimeRate - float
						  @Note , -- Note - nvarchar(max)
						  @CreatedBy, -- CreatedBy - bigint
						  GETDATE() , -- CreatedDate - datetime
						  0  -- IsDeleted - bit
						)
					SET @Id=SCOPE_IDENTITY()
					IF((SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM  @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType)>0)
					BEGIN
						INSERT INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper
								( HolidayId ,
								  DesistRegimeId ,
								  Date ,
								  IsDeleted
								)
						SELECT   @Id , -- HolidayId - bigint
								  WHDMT.DesistRegimeId , -- DesistRegimeId - bigint
								  WHDMT.Date , -- Date - datetime
								  0  -- IsDeleted - bit
						FROM @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType  WHDMT  
					END
				END
				ELSE
				BEGIN
					UPDATE dbo.Data_Workingday_Holiday 
							SET Name=@Name,
								ClassifyId=@ClassifyId,
								IsAnnualLeave=@IsAnnualLeave,
								SalaryRegimeId=@SalaryRegimeId,
								OvertimeRate=@OvertimeRate,
								Note=@Note			
					WHERE Id=@Id

					UPDATE dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper SET IsDeleted=1 WHERE HolidayId=@Id

					UPDATE DWHM
						SET DWHM.IsDeleted=0,
							DWHM.DesistRegimeId=WHMT.DesistRegimeId
					FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper DWHM
					INNER JOIN @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType WHMT ON WHMT.Id = DWHM.Id
					
					IF((SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM  @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType WHERE Id=0)>0)
					BEGIN
						INSERT INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper
								( HolidayId ,
								  DesistRegimeId ,
								  Date ,
								  IsDeleted
								)
						SELECT   @Id , -- HolidayId - bigint
								  WHDMT.DesistRegimeId , -- DesistRegimeId - bigint
								  WHDMT.Date , -- Date - datetime
								  0  -- IsDeleted - bit
						FROM @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType WHDMT
						LEFT JOIN Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper DWH on DWH.HolidayId=@Id AND DWH.Date=WHDMT.Date
						WHERE WHDMT.Id=0 AND ISNULL(DWH.Id,0)=0

						UPDATE DWHM
								SET DWHM.IsDeleted=0,
							DWHM.DesistRegimeId=WHMT.DesistRegimeId
							FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper DWHM
							LEFT JOIN @WorkingdayHolidayMapperType WHMT ON WHMT.Id=0
							LEFT JOIN dbo.Data_Workingday_HolidayMapper DWHM1 ON DWHM1.Date=DWHM.Date AND DWHM1.HolidayId=@Id AND DWHM1.IsDeleted=1
						WHERE WHMT.Id=0 AND DWHM1.Id<>0 
					END
				END															
			'
		SET @params =' @Id BIGINT,@Name NVARCHAR(500),@ClassifyId BIGINT,@IsAnnualLeave	BIT, @SalaryRegimeId BIGINT,@OvertimeRate FLOAT,@Note NVARCHAR(500),@CreatedBy BIGINT,@WorkingdayHolidayMapperType WorkingdayHolidayMapperType READONLY'
		EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery,@params,@Id,@Name,@ClassifyId,@IsAnnualLeave, @SalaryRegimeId,@OvertimeRate,@Note,@CreatedBy,@WorkingdayHolidayMapperType
	
END
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Del_DeleteWorkingdayShift]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Del_DeleteWorkingdayShift]
	@Id					BIGINT,
	@DbName				VARCHAR(500)
as
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'							
						--DELETE FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift WHERE ShiftId=@Id	

						UPDATE dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift SET IsDeleted=1 WHERE ShiftId=@Id	
						UPDATE dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift_Detail SET IsDeleted=1 WHERE ShiffId=@Id
					'
	SET @params = '@Id BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@Id

END

/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Get_GetWorkingdayShift]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
 

/*
***************************************************************************
	-- Author:			nhungpt
	-- Description:		Update User
	-- Date				21/11/2019					Update record
***************************************************************************
*/
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Get_GetWorkingdayShift]
	@BaseParam BaseParamType READONLY,	
	@TotalRecord int = 0 output
AS
--begin try
	DECLARE @FilterField		NVARCHAR(MAX) = '',
			@OrderBy			VARCHAR(100) = '',
			@PageNumber			INT = 1,
			@PageSize			INT = 9000000,
			@UserId				INT = 1,
			@RoleId				INT = 1,
			@DBName				NVARCHAR(50) = 'Hrm_System',
			@LanguageId			INT = 1
		IF EXISTS(SELECT TOP 1 * FROM @BaseParam)
		BEGIN
			SELECT TOP 1 @FilterField = FilterField,
						 @OrderBy	  = OrderBy,	
						 @PageNumber  = PageNumber,
						 @PageSize	  = PageSize,
						 @UserId	  = UserId,	
						 @RoleId	  = RoleId,
						 @DbName	  = DbName,	
						 @LanguageId  = LanguageId	
			FROM @BaseParam
		END
		declare	@WhereSQL				nvarchar(max),
				@Delim					nvarchar(100),
				@StartIndex				bigint,
				
				@EndIndex				bigint,
				@SQL					nvarchar(max),
				@SQLCount					nvarchar(max),
				@SQLFrom				nvarchar(max),
				@SQLSelect					nvarchar(max),
				
				@dynamicsql				nvarchar(max),
				@dynamicparamdec		nvarchar(max),
				@SearchResult			bigint,
				@OrderBySQL				varchar(max),
				@WhereSQLRight				nvarchar(max)

		set		@OrderBy				= isnull(@OrderBy,' DWS.Id desc')
		set		@FilterField			= isnull(@FilterField,'')
		set		@WhereSQL				= ' ' 
		set		@WhereSQLRight			=''
		set		@PageNumber				= case when isnull(@PageNumber,0)	= 0 then 1 else convert(int,@PageNumber) end
		set		@PageSize				= case when isnull(@PageSize,0)	= 0 then 50 else convert(int,@PageSize) end

		--1. Calculate to paging
		set		@StartIndex				= @PageSize * @PageNumber
		set		@EndIndex				= @StartIndex + @PageSize

		set		@StartIndex				= ((@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) + 1
		set		@EndIndex				= @PageNumber * @PageSize

		if @FilterField <> ''
			begin
				set	@Delim				= ' '
				set	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @FilterField
			end
		--2. get right for role or user

		-- set @WhereSQLRight by role or user

		if @WhereSQLRight <> ''
			begin
				set	@Delim				= ' '
				set	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @WhereSQLRight
			end

		--3. Build select query

			set	@SQLSelect						= 
			N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
				SELECT s.[ShiftId]
					  ,s.[ShiftId] AS Id
					  ,s.[Name]
					  ,s.[PeriodId]
					  ,s.[DatabaseName]
					  ,s.[IsOverNight]
					  ,s.[LateAllowed]
					  ,s.[EarlyAllowed]
					  ,s.Status
					  ,s.IsDefault
					  ,DWP.Name	AS PeriodName														
			'				
	  set @SQLFrom=' FROM [dbo].[Data_Workingday_Shift]	s
					 LEFT JOIN dbo.Data_Workingday_Period DWP ON DWP.AutoId=s.PeriodId '

	  set @SQL=@SQLSelect + @SQLFrom+ ' WHERE s.IsDeleted = 0 ' +@WhereSQL + 
	   ' ORDER BY s.ShiftId DESC
		  OFFSET  '+ convert(varchar,(@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) +' ROWS  FETCH NEXT '+ convert(varchar,@PageSize) +' ROWS ONLY '
		  
		  EXEC(@SQL )
		  PRINT @SQL
		--4. Count
		set @SQLCount=N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + ' SELECT @TotalRecord = COUNT(s.ShiftId) '
		set @dynamicsql=@SQLCount + @SQLFrom+ '  WHERE s.IsDeleted = 0 ' +@WhereSQL
		set @dynamicparamdec = '@TotalRecord INT OUTPUT'
		execute sp_executesql @dynamicsql,@dynamicparamdec,@TotalRecord  OUTPUT

	--end try

	--begin catch

	--	declare	@ErrorNum				int,
	--			@ErrorMsg				varchar(200),
	--			@ErrorProc				varchar(50),
	--			@SessionId				int,
	--			@AddlInfo				varchar(max)

	--	set @ErrorNum					= error_number()
	--	set @ErrorMsg					= 'System_Get_GetAllData_Organization: ' + error_message()
	--	set @ErrorProc					= error_procedure()
	--	set @AddlInfo					= '@OrderBy=' + @OrderBy

	--	exec utl_Insert_ErrorLog @ErrorNum,@DbName, @ErrorMsg, @ErrorProc, 'Data_Staff_Information', 'GET', @SessionId, @AddlInfo

	--end catch
	 
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Get_GetWorkingdayShiftById]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Get_GetWorkingdayShiftById]
	@Id BIGINT,
	@DbName NVARCHAR(100)
as
 
BEGIN	

	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'			
				SELECT DWS.[ShiftId]
					  ,DWS.[ShiftId] AS Id
					  ,DWS.[Name]
					  ,DWS.[PeriodId]
					  ,DWS.[DatabaseName]
					  ,DWS.[IsOverNight]
					  ,DWS.[LateAllowed]
					  ,DWS.[EarlyAllowed]
					  ,DWS.[WorkId]
					  ,DWS.Status
					  ,DWS.IsDefault
					  ,DWS.ToShift
					  ,DWS.FromShift
			 FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift	DWS
			 WHERE DWS.ShiftId=@Id and DWS.IsDeleted=0
		'
	SET @params = '@Id BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@Id

END

CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Get_GetWorkingdayShiftDetailByShiftId]
	@ShiftId BIGINT,
	@DbName NVARCHAR(100)
as
 
BEGIN	

	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'	
				SELECT 		
					DWSD.[Id],
					DWSD.[ShiffId],
					DWSD.[StartTime],
					DWSD.[EndTime],
					DWSD.[TotalTime],
					DWSD.[StartDate],
					DWSD.[EndDate],
					DWSD.[Status],
					DWSD.[OvertimeMinRequire],
					DWSD.[SalaryRatio],
					DWSD.[IsLunchBreak],
					DWSD.[IsOverTime],
					DWSD.[T2],
					DWSD.[T3],
					DWSD.[T4],
					DWSD.[T5],
					DWSD.[T6],
					DWSD.[T7],
					DWSD.[CN]
				FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift_Detail DWSD
				WHERE DWSD.ShiffId=@ShiftId and DWSD.IsDeleted=0 
		'
	SET @params = '@ShiftId BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@ShiftId

END

/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Update_SaveWorkingdayShift]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdayShift_Update_SaveWorkingdayShift]
	 @Id BIGINT,
     @Name NVARCHAR(500),
     @PeriodId BIGINT,
     @DatabaseName	NVARCHAR(500),
     @IsOverNight BIT,
     @LateAllowed DECIMAL(18,2),
	 @EarlyAllowed DECIMAL(18,2),
     @WorkId  BIGINT,	
     @Status BIGINT,
	 @IsDefault BIT,
	 @ToShift TIME(7),
	 @FromShift TIME(7),
	 @CreatedBy BIGINT,
     @DbName NVARCHAR(500),
     @WorkingdayShiftDetailType WorkingdayShiftDetailType READONLY
AS
 

BEGIN
	 
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)	   				
															 
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
				
				IF(@Id=0)
				BEGIN
					INSERT INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift
							 ( Name ,
							   PeriodId ,
							   DatabaseName ,
							   IsOverNight ,
							   LateAllowed ,
							   EarlyAllowed ,
							   ToShift,
							   FromShift,
							   WorkId ,
							   Status ,
							   IsDefault,
							   IsDeleted
							 )
					 VALUES  ( @Name , -- Name - nvarchar(50)
							   @PeriodId , -- PeriodId - bigint
							   @DbName , -- DatabaseName - varchar(50)
							   @IsOverNight , -- IsOverNight - bit
							   @LateAllowed , -- LateAllowed - decimal
							   @EarlyAllowed  , -- EarlyAllowed - decimal
							   @ToShift,
							   @FromShift,
							   @WorkId, -- WorkId - bigint
							   @Status , -- Status - bigint
							   @IsDefault , -- IsDefault - bit
							   0  -- IsDeleted - bit
							 )

					SET @Id=SCOPE_IDENTITY()
					IF((SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM @WorkingdayShiftDetailType WHERE Id=0)>0)
					BEGIN
						 INSERT INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift_Detail
								 ( ShiffId ,
								   StartTime ,
								   EndTime ,
								   TotalTime ,
								   StartDate ,
								   Status ,
								   OvertimeMinRequire ,
								   SalaryRatio ,
								   IsLunchBreak ,
								   IsOverTime ,
								   T2 ,
								   T3 ,
								   T4 ,
								   T5 ,
								   T6 ,
								   T7 ,
								   CN,
								   IsDeleted
								 )
						 SELECT   @Id , -- ShiffId - bigint
								   WSDT.StartTime, -- StartTime - time
								   WSDT.EndTime , -- EndTime - time
								   WSDT.TotalTime , -- TotalTime - decimal
								   GETDATE() , -- StartDate - date
								   1, -- Status - int
								   WSDT.OvertimeMinRequire , -- OvertimeMinRequire - decimal
								   IIF(WSDT.IsOverTime=1,WSDT.SalaryRatio *   0.001,0) , -- SalaryRatio - decimal
								   WSDT.IsLunchBreak , -- IsLunchBreak - bit
								   WSDT.IsOverTime , -- IsOverTime - bit
								   WSDT.T2 , -- T2 - bit
								   WSDT.T3 , -- T3 - bit
								   WSDT.T4 , -- T4 - bit
								   WSDT.T5 , -- T5 - bit
								   WSDT.T6 , -- T6 - bit
								   WSDT.T7 , -- T7 - bit
								   WSDT.CN, -- CN - bit
								   0
						FROM @WorkingdayShiftDetailType WSDT
					END
				END
				ELSE
				BEGIN
					 UPDATE dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift
							SET Name=@Name ,
								PeriodId=@PeriodId,
								DatabaseName= @DbName,
								IsOverNight=@IsOverNight,	
								LateAllowed=@LateAllowed,
								EarlyAllowed=@EarlyAllowed,
								ToShift=@ToShift,
								FromShift=@FromShift,
								WorkId=@WorkId,
								Status=@Status,
								IsDefault=@IsDefault
					WHERE ShiftId=@Id
					 
					UPDATE dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift_Detail SET IsDeleted=1 WHERE ShiffId=@Id

					UPDATE DWSD
							SET 
								DWSD.StartTime=DWSDT.StartTime,
								DWSD.EndTime=DWSDT.EndTime,
								DWSD.TotalTime=DWSDT.TotalTime,
								DWSD.Status=1,
								DWSD.OvertimeMinRequire=DWSDT.OvertimeMinRequire,
								DWSD.SalaryRatio=IIF(DWSDT.IsOverTime=1,DWSDT.SalaryRatio *   0.001,0),
								DWSD.IsLunchBreak=DWSDT.IsLunchBreak,
								DWSD.IsOverTime=DWSDT.IsOverTime,
								DWSD.T2=DWSDT.T2,
								DWSD.T3=DWSDT.T3,
								DWSD.T4=DWSDT.T4,
								DWSD.T5=DWSDT.T5,
								DWSD.T6=DWSDT.T6,
								DWSD.T7=DWSDT.T7,
								DWSD.CN=DWSDT.CN,
								DWSD.IsDeleted=0
					FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift_Detail DWSD
					INNER JOIN @WorkingdayShiftDetailType DWSDT ON DWSDT.Id=DWSD.Id

					IF((SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM @WorkingdayShiftDetailType WHERE Id=0)>0)
					BEGIN
						 INSERT INTO dbo.Data_Workingday_Shift_Detail
								 ( ShiffId ,
								   StartTime ,
								   EndTime ,
								   TotalTime ,
								   StartDate ,
								   Status ,
								   OvertimeMinRequire ,
								   SalaryRatio ,
								   IsLunchBreak ,
								   IsOverTime ,
								   T2 ,
								   T3 ,
								   T4 ,
								   T5 ,
								   T6 ,
								   T7 ,
								   CN ,
								   IsDeleted
								 )
						 SELECT   @Id , -- ShiffId - bigint
								   WSDT.StartTime, -- StartTime - time
								   WSDT.EndTime , -- EndTime - time
								   WSDT.TotalTime , -- TotalTime - decimal
								   GETDATE() , -- StartDate - date
								   1, -- Status - int
								   WSDT.OvertimeMinRequire , -- OvertimeMinRequire - decimal
								   IIF(WSDT.IsOverTime=1,WSDT.SalaryRatio *   0.001,0) , -- SalaryRatio - decimal
								   WSDT.IsLunchBreak , -- IsLunchBreak - bit
								   WSDT.IsOverTime , -- IsOverTime - bit
								   WSDT.T2 , -- T2 - bit
								   WSDT.T3 , -- T3 - bit
								   WSDT.T4 , -- T4 - bit
								   WSDT.T5 , -- T5 - bit
								   WSDT.T6 , -- T6 - bit
								   WSDT.T7 , -- T7 - bit
								   WSDT.CN ,-- CN - bit
								   0
						FROM @WorkingdayShiftDetailType WSDT
						WHERE WSDT.Id=0
					END

				END
																		
			'
		SET @params ='@Id BIGINT,@Name NVARCHAR(500),@PeriodId BIGINT,@DatabaseName	NVARCHAR(500),@IsOverNight BIT,@LateAllowed DECIMAL(18,2), @EarlyAllowed DECIMAL(18,2),@WorkId  BIGINT,
		  @Status BIGINT, @IsDefault BIT,@ToShift TIME(7),@FromShift TIME(7), @CreatedBy BIGINT,@DbName NVARCHAR(500), @WorkingdayShiftDetailType WorkingdayShiftDetailType READONLY'
		EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery,@params,@Id,@Name,@PeriodId,@DatabaseName,@IsOverNight,@LateAllowed,@EarlyAllowed,@WorkId,@Status,@IsDefault,@ToShift,@FromShift,@CreatedBy,@DbName,@WorkingdayShiftDetailType
	
END
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdaySummary_Get_GetWorkingdayAllStaff]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdaySummary_Get_GetWorkingdayAllStaff]
	@BaseParam BaseParamType READONLY,
	@TotalRecord int = 0 output
AS
BEGIN TRY
	DECLARE @FilterField		NVARCHAR(MAX) = '',
			@OrderBy			VARCHAR(100) = '',
			@PageNumber			INT = 1,
			@PageSize			INT = 9000000,
			@UserId				INT = 1,
			@RoleId				INT = 1,
			@DBName				NVARCHAR(50) = 'Hrm_System',
			@LanguageId			INT = 1
		IF EXISTS(SELECT TOP 1 * FROM @BaseParam)
		BEGIN
			SELECT TOP 1 @FilterField = FilterField,
						 @OrderBy	  = OrderBy,	
						 @PageNumber  = PageNumber,
						 @PageSize	  = PageSize,
						 @UserId	  = UserId,	
						 @RoleId	  = RoleId,
						 @DbName	  = DbName,	
						 @LanguageId  = LanguageId	
			FROM @BaseParam
		END
		DECLARE	@WhereSQL				NVARCHAR(MAX),
				@Delim					NVARCHAR(100),
				@StartIndex				BIGINT,
				
				@EndIndex				BIGINT,
				@SQL					NVARCHAR(MAX),
				@SQLCount				NVARCHAR(MAX),
				@SQLFrom				NVARCHAR(MAX),
				@SQLSelect				NVARCHAR(MAX),
				
				@dynamicsql				NVARCHAR(MAX),
				@dynamicparamdec		NVARCHAR(MAX),
				@SearchResult			BIGINT,
				@OrderBySQL				VARCHAR(MAX),
				@WhereSQLRight			NVARCHAR(MAX)

		SET		@OrderBy				= ISNULL(@OrderBy,' Id desc')
		SET		@FilterField			= ISNULL(@FilterField,'')
		SET		@WhereSQL				= ' ' 
		SET		@WhereSQLRight			=''
		SET		@PageNumber				= CASE WHEN ISNULL(@PageNumber,0)	= 0 THEN 1 ELSE CONVERT(int,@PageNumber) END
		SET		@PageSize				= CASE WHEN ISNULL(@PageSize,0)	= 0 THEN 50 ELSE CONVERT(int,@PageSize) END

		--1. Calculate to paging
		SET		@StartIndex				= @PageSize * @PageNumber
		SET		@EndIndex				= @StartIndex + @PageSize

		SET		@StartIndex				= ((@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) + 1
		SET		@EndIndex				= @PageNumber * @PageSize

		IF @FilterField <> ''
			BEGIN
				SET	@Delim				= ' '
				SET	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @FilterField
			END
		--2. get right for role or user

		-- set @WhereSQLRight by role or user

		IF @WhereSQLRight <> ''
			BEGIN
				SET	@Delim				= ' '
				SET	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @WhereSQLRight
			END

		--3. Build select query
		-- FilterField ex: DSP.ParentId = @StaffId AND MONTH(DWS.Date) = @Month AND YEAR(DWS.Date) = @Year 
		-- p/s: For login Staff only add at the end of FilterField "AND DWS.StaffId = @StaffId"
		SET	@SQLSelect = 
			N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
			SELECT 
				DWS.StaffId AS Id,
				DSI.Name,
				DWS.StandardWorkingday,
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.TotalWorkingday, 0)) AS TotalWorkingday,
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.Workingday,0)) AS Workingday,
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.WorkingdayOvertime, 0)) AS WorkingdayOvertime,
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.WorkingdayAnnualLeave,0)) AS WorkingdayAnnualLeave,
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.WorkingdaySupplement, 0)) AS WorkingdaySupplement,	
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.WorkingdayUnpaidLeave, 0)) AS WorkingdayUnpaidLeave,
				SUM(ISNULL(DWS.OtherWorkingday, 0)) AS OtherWorkingday,
				ISNULL(SUM(DATEDIFF(MINUTE, ''00:00:00.000'', CAST(DWS.EarlyDuration AS TIME))), 0) + ISNULL(SUM(DATEDIFF(MINUTE, ''00:00:00.000'', CAST(DWS.LateDuration AS TIME))), 0) AS TotalLateEarly
			FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary DWS
			INNER JOIN dbo.Data_Staff_Parent DSP ON DWS.StaffId = DSP.StaffId
			INNER JOIN dbo.Data_Staff_Information DSI ON DSI.Id = DWS.StaffId
			WHERE ' +@WhereSQL + '
			GROUP BY DWS.StaffId, DSI.Name, DWS.StandardWorkingday
			ORDER BY ' + @OrderBy+ ' 
			OFFSET  '+ CONVERT(VARCHAR,(@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) +' ROWS  FETCH NEXT '+ CONVERT(VARCHAR,@PageSize) +' ROWS ONLY
			'	
		PRINT (@SQLSelect)	  
		EXEC(@SQLSelect)

		--4. Count
		SET @SQLCount=N'
			USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
			SELECT 
			@TotalRecord =COUNT(DISTINCT DWS.StaffId)
			FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary DWS
			INNER JOIN dbo.Data_Staff_Parent DSP ON DWS.StaffId = DSP.StaffId
			WHERE ' +@WhereSQL
			PRINT(@SQLCount)
		SET @dynamicparamdec = '@TotalRecord INT OUTPUT'
		EXEC sp_executesql @SQLCount,@dynamicparamdec,@TotalRecord  OUTPUT

	END TRY

	BEGIN CATCH

		DECLARE	@ErrorNum				INT,
				@ErrorMsg				VARCHAR(200),
				@ErrorProc				VARCHAR(50),
				@SessionId				INT,
				@AddlInfo				VARCHAR(MAX)

		SET @ErrorNum					= ERROR_NUMBER()
		SET @ErrorMsg					= 'Workingday_Get_GetWorkingdayAllStaff: ' + ERROR_MESSAGE()
		SET @ErrorProc					= ERROR_PROCEDURE()
		SET @AddlInfo					= '@OrderBy=' + @OrderBy

		EXEC utl_Insert_ErrorLog @ErrorNum,@DbName, @ErrorMsg, @ErrorProc, 'Workingday_Get_GetWorkingdayAllStaff', 'GET', @SessionId, @AddlInfo

	END CATCH
	 
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdaySummary_Get_GetWorkingdayByStaffAndMonth]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdaySummary_Get_GetWorkingdayByStaffAndMonth]
	@StaffId					BIGINT,
	@Month  					INT,
	@Year  						INT,
	@DbName						VARCHAR(500)
as
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'	
						--SELECT 
						--	*							
						--FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary
						--WHERE StaffId = @StaffId AND MONTH(Date) = @Month AND YEAR(Date) = @Year


						DECLARE @FromDay BIGINT=(SELECT FromDay FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period  WHERE IsDefault=1)
						DECLARE @ToDay BIGINT=(SELECT Today FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period  WHERE IsDefault=1)

						IF((@FromDay-@ToDay)>0)
						BEGIN
								SELECT 
									*							
								FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary
								WHERE StaffId = @StaffId AND (MONTH(Date) = @Month AND DAY(Date)<@ToDay OR MONTH(Date) = (@Month-1) AND DAY(Date)>=@FromDay) AND YEAR(Date) = @Year 
						END
						ELSE IF ((@FromDay-@ToDay)<0)
						BEGIN
							SELECT 
								*							
							FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary
							WHERE StaffId = @StaffId AND (MONTH(Date) = @Month AND DAY(Date)>=@FromDay AND  DAY(Date)<=@ToDay  ) AND YEAR(Date) = @Year 
						END
					'
					PRINT @ExeQuery
	SET @params = '@StaffId	BIGINT,	@Month INT,	@Year INT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@StaffId, @Month, @Year

END
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdaySummary_Get_GetWorkingdaySummaryFinal]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
 

/*
***************************************************************************
	-- Author:			nhungpt
	-- Description:		Update User
	-- Date				21/11/2019					Update record
***************************************************************************
*/
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdaySummary_Get_GetWorkingdaySummaryFinal]
	@BaseParam BaseParamType READONLY,
	@StaffId  					BIGINT,
	@Month  					INT,
	@Year  						INT,	
	@OutTotalJson				NVARCHAR(MAX)='' OUTPUT,
	@TotalRecord int = 0 output
AS
--begin try
	DECLARE @FilterField		NVARCHAR(MAX) = '',
			@OrderBy			VARCHAR(100) = '',
			@PageNumber			INT = 1,
			@PageSize			INT = 9000000,
			@UserId				INT = 1,
			@RoleId				INT = 1,
			@DBName				NVARCHAR(50) = 'Hrm_System',
			@LanguageId			INT = 1
		IF EXISTS(SELECT TOP 1 * FROM @BaseParam)
		BEGIN
			SELECT TOP 1 @FilterField = FilterField,
						 @OrderBy	  = OrderBy,	
						 @PageNumber  = PageNumber,
						 @PageSize	  = PageSize,
						 @UserId	  = UserId,	
						 @RoleId	  = RoleId,
						 @DbName	  = DbName,	
						 @LanguageId  = LanguageId	
			FROM @BaseParam
		END
		declare	@WhereSQL				nvarchar(max),
				@Delim					nvarchar(100),
				@StartIndex				bigint,
				
				@EndIndex				bigint,
				@SQL					nvarchar(max),
				@SQLCount					nvarchar(max),
				@SQLFrom				nvarchar(max),
				@SQLSelect					nvarchar(max),
				
				@dynamicsql				nvarchar(max),
				@dynamicparamdec		nvarchar(max),
				@SearchResult			bigint,
				@OrderBySQL				varchar(max),
				@WhereSQLRight				nvarchar(max)

		set		@OrderBy				= isnull(@OrderBy,' DWS.Id desc')
		set		@FilterField			= isnull(@FilterField,'')
		set		@WhereSQL				= ' ' 
		set		@WhereSQLRight			=''
		set		@PageNumber				= case when isnull(@PageNumber,0)	= 0 then 1 else convert(int,@PageNumber) end
		set		@PageSize				= case when isnull(@PageSize,0)	= 0 then 50 else convert(int,@PageSize) end

		--1. Calculate to paging
		set		@StartIndex				= @PageSize * @PageNumber
		set		@EndIndex				= @StartIndex + @PageSize

		set		@StartIndex				= ((@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) + 1
		set		@EndIndex				= @PageNumber * @PageSize

		if @FilterField <> ''
			begin
				set	@Delim				= ' '
				set	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @FilterField
			end
		--2. get right for role or user

		-- set @WhereSQLRight by role or user

		if @WhereSQLRight <> ''
			begin
				set	@Delim				= ' '
				set	@WhereSQL			= @WhereSQL + @Delim +  @WhereSQLRight
			end
		
		IF(@Month=0)
		BEGIN
			SET @Month=MONTH(GETDATE())

		END
		IF(@Year=0)
		BEGIN
			SET @Year=YEAR(GETDATE())

		END

		--3. Build select query

			set	@SQLSelect						= 
			N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'
						DECLARE @FromDay BIGINT=(SELECT FromDay FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period  WHERE IsDefault=1)
						DECLARE @ToDay BIGINT=(SELECT Today FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period  WHERE IsDefault=1)
										
						IF((@FromDay-@ToDay)>0)
						BEGIN								
								SELECT 
									DWS.*,
									(SELECT COUNT(S.Id) FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Supplement S WHERE DWS.Date=S.Date AND S.IsDeleted=0 )	AS CountWorkingdaySupplement						
								FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary DWS
								WHERE DWS.StaffId = '+ convert(varchar,@StaffId)+' AND (MONTH(DWS.Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Month)+' AND DAY(DWS.Date)<@ToDay OR MONTH(DWS.Date) = ('+ convert(varchar,@Month)+'-1) AND DAY(DWS.Date)>=@FromDay) AND YEAR(DWS.Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Year)+' ORDER BY DWS.Date DESC
		  OFFSET  '+ convert(varchar,(@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) +' ROWS  FETCH NEXT '+ convert(varchar,@PageSize) +' ROWS ONLY 
						END
						ELSE IF ((@FromDay-@ToDay)<0)
						BEGIN
							SELECT 
								DWS.*,
								(SELECT COUNT(S.Id) FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Supplement S WHERE DWS.Date=S.Date AND S.IsDeleted=0 )	AS CountWorkingdaySupplement				
							FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary DWS
							WHERE DWS.StaffId = '+ convert(varchar,@StaffId)+' AND (MONTH(DWS.Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Month)+' AND DAY(DWS.Date)>=@FromDay AND  DAY(DWS.Date)<=@ToDay  ) AND YEAR(DWS.Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Year)+'  ORDER BY DWS.Date DESC
		  OFFSET  '+ convert(varchar,(@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) +' ROWS  FETCH NEXT '+ convert(varchar,@PageSize) +' ROWS ONLY 
						END	
													
			'				
	  set @SQL=@SQLSelect
	  -- ' ORDER BY DWS.CreatedDate DESC
		 -- OFFSET  '+ convert(varchar,(@PageNumber - 1) * @PageSize) +' ROWS  FETCH NEXT '+ convert(varchar,@PageSize) +' ROWS ONLY '
		  
		  EXEC(@SQL )
		--4. Count
		set @SQLCount=N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + '  

				DECLARE @FromDay BIGINT=(SELECT FromDay FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period  WHERE IsDefault=1)
						DECLARE @ToDay BIGINT=(SELECT Today FROM  dbo.Data_Workingday_Period  WHERE IsDefault=1)

						IF((@FromDay-@ToDay)>0)
						BEGIN														 
							BEGIN								
								SELECT 
									@TotalRecord=COUNT(Id)							
								FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary 
								WHERE StaffId = '+ convert(varchar,@StaffId)+' AND (MONTH(Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Month)+' AND DAY(Date)<@ToDay OR MONTH(Date) = ('+ convert(varchar,@Month)+'-1) AND DAY(Date)>=@FromDay) AND YEAR(Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Year)+'
							END
						END
						ELSE IF ((@FromDay-@ToDay)<0)
						BEGIN
							SELECT
								@TotalRecord=COUNT(Id)							
							FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary
							WHERE StaffId = '+ convert(varchar,@StaffId)+' AND (MONTH(Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Month)+' AND DAY(Date)>=@FromDay AND  DAY(Date)<=@ToDay  ) AND YEAR(Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Year)+'
						END	
		'


		SET @SQLSelect=N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + '

				DECLARE @Data table(
					TotalWorkingday FLOAT,
					TotalLateDuration FLOAT,
					TotalEarlyDuration FLOAT,
					TotalWorkingdayOvertime FLOAT,
					TotalWorkingdaySupplement FLOAT,
					TotalLateEarlyDuration FLOAT
				)

				INSERT INTO @Data
						( TotalWorkingday ,
						  TotalLateDuration ,
						  TotalEarlyDuration ,
						  TotalWorkingdayOvertime ,
						  TotalWorkingdaySupplement ,
						  TotalLateEarlyDuration
						)
				SELECT  SUM(TotalWorkingday), -- TotalWorkingday - float
						  SUM(DATEDIFF(MINUTE,''00:00:00'',CONVERT(CHAR(8),DWS.LateDuration,108))) , -- TotalLateDuration - float
						  SUM(DATEDIFF(MINUTE,''00:00:00'',CONVERT(CHAR(8),DWS.EarlyDuration,108))) , -- TotalEarlyDuration - float
						  SUM(WorkingdayOvertime) , -- TotalWorkingdayOvertime - float
						  SUM(DW.a) , -- TotalWorkingdaySupplement - float
						  0.0 -- TotalLateEarlyDuration - float
				FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Summary DWS
				OUTER APPLY(SELECT COUNT(Id) AS a FROM Data_WorkingDay_Supplement S WHERE S.Date=DWS.Date AND S.IsDeleted=0) DW
				WHERE StaffId = '+ convert(varchar,@StaffId)+' AND (MONTH(Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Month)+' AND DAY(Date)<@ToDay OR MONTH(Date) = ('+ convert(varchar,@Month)+'-1) AND DAY(Date)>=@FromDay) AND YEAR(Date) = '+ convert(varchar,@Year)+'
							
				SET @OutTotalJson=''{TotalWorkingday:'' + CAST((SELECT TotalWorkingday FROM @Data) as NVARCHAR) + '',TotalWorkingdayOvertime:''+ CAST((SELECT TotalWorkingdayOvertime FROM @Data) as NVARCHAR) + '',TotalLateDuration:''+ CAST((SELECT TotalLateDuration FROM @Data) as NVARCHAR) + '',TotalEarlyDuration:''+ CAST((SELECT TotalEarlyDuration FROM @Data) as NVARCHAR) + '',TotalWorkingdaySupplement:''+ CAST((SELECT TotalWorkingdaySupplement FROM @Data) as NVARCHAR) + ''}''
				
		'
		set @dynamicsql=@SQLCount +@SQLSelect
		PRINT @dynamicsql
		set @dynamicparamdec = '@StaffId BIGINT,@Month INT,@Year INT,@OutTotalJson NVARCHAR(MAX) OUTPUT,@TotalRecord INT OUTPUT'
		execute sp_executesql @dynamicsql,@dynamicparamdec,@StaffId,@Month,@Year,@OutTotalJson OUTPUT,@TotalRecord OUTPUT

	--end try

	--begin catch

	--	declare	@ErrorNum				int,
	--			@ErrorMsg				varchar(200),
	--			@ErrorProc				varchar(50),
	--			@SessionId				int,
	--			@AddlInfo				varchar(max)

	--	set @ErrorNum					= error_number()
	--	set @ErrorMsg					= 'System_Get_GetAllData_Organization: ' + error_message()
	--	set @ErrorProc					= error_procedure()
	--	set @AddlInfo					= '@OrderBy=' + @OrderBy

	--	exec utl_Insert_ErrorLog @ErrorNum,@DbName, @ErrorMsg, @ErrorProc, 'Data_Staff_Information', 'GET', @SessionId, @AddlInfo

	--end catch
	 
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdaySupplement_Del_DeleteListWorkingDaySupplement]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdaySupplement_Del_DeleteListWorkingDaySupplement]
	@ListStringId			NVARCHAR(500),
	@StaffId				BIGINT,
	@DbName					NVARCHAR(500)
as
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'							
						
						DECLARE @Check BIT=1

						DECLARE @data TABLE(
							RequestId BIGINT,
							RequestStatusId BIGINT
						)

						INSERT INTO @data
								( RequestId )
						SELECT   S.Name  -- id - bigint
						FROM dbo.splitstring(@ListStringId,'','') S

						UPDATE D
							SET D.RequestStatusId=DWSA.RequestStatusId
						FROM @data D
						OUTER APPLY(SELECT TOP 1.* FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Supplement_Approval WHERE RequestId=D.RequestId ORDER BY ApprovedDate DESC) DWSA


						DECLARE @RequestId BIGINT
						DECLARE @RequestStatusId BIGINT

						DECLARE @IsRole BIGINT
						DECLARE @IsUser BIGINT

						DECLARE WorkingdaySupplement CURSOR FOR
						SELECT RequestId,RequestStatusId FROM @data

						OPEN WorkingdaySupplement

						FETCH NEXT FROM WorkingdaySupplement
							INTO @RequestId,@RequestStatusId

						WHILE @@FETCH_STATUS = 0
							BEGIN	
								
								SET @IsUser=(SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Supplement_Configuration WHERE RequesterId=@StaffId AND RequesterTypeId=269 
								AND CurrentRequestStatusId=@RequestStatusId AND RequestActionId=331 AND NextRequestStatusId IS NULL AND IsDeleted=0)

								SET @IsRole=(SELECT COUNT(Id) FROM dbo.Data_Workingday_Supplement_Configuration WHERE RequesterId=@StaffId AND RequesterTypeId=270 
								AND CurrentRequestStatusId=@RequestStatusId AND RequestActionId=331 AND NextRequestStatusId IS NULL AND IsDeleted=0)

								IF(@IsUser=0 AND @IsRole=0)
								BEGIN
									SET @Check=0
									BREAK
								END																							
																					
								FETCH NEXT FROM WorkingdaySupplement
								INTO @RequestId,@RequestStatusId
							END
						CLOSE WorkingdaySupplement
						DEALLOCATE WorkingdaySupplement

						print @Check
						IF(@Check=0)
						BEGIN
							SELECT 
									DWS.* ,
									D.RequestStatusId
							FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Supplement DWS
							INNER JOIN @data D ON D.RequestId=DWS.Id
							LEFT JOIN Data_Workingday_Supplement_Configuration DWSC on DWSC.RequesterId=@StaffId 
							AND (DWSC.RequesterTypeId=269 or DWSC.RequesterTypeId=270)
							AND DWSC.CurrentRequestStatusId=D.RequestStatusId 
							AND DWSC.NextRequestStatusId IS NULL 
							AND DWSC.RequestActionId=331 AND DWSC.IsDeleted=0	
							WHERE ISNULL(DWSC.Id,0)=0						
						END
						ELSE
						BEGIN
							--DELETE 
							--FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Supplement DWS
							--INNER JOIN @data D ON D.RequestId=DWS.Id

							UPDATE DWS
								SET DWS.IsDeleted=1
							FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Supplement DWS
							INNER JOIN @data D ON D.RequestId=DWS.Id
						END
					'
	SET @params = '@ListStringId NVARCHAR(500),@StaffId BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@ListStringId,@StaffId

END
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[WorkingdaySupplement_Del_DeleteWorkingDaySupplement]    Script Date: 2/7/2020 6:02:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON

CREATE PROCEDURE[dbo].[WorkingdaySupplement_Del_DeleteWorkingDaySupplement]
	@Id					BIGINT,
	@DbName				VARCHAR(500)
as
 
BEGIN
	DECLARE @ExeQuery NVARCHAR(MAX), @params NVARCHAR(MAX)
	SET @ExeQuery = N'USE [Hrm_'+ @DbName + ']' + N'							
						DELETE FROM dbo.Data_WorkingDay_Supplement WHERE Id=@Id	
					'
	SET @params = '@Id BIGINT'
	EXEC sp_executesql @ExeQuery, @params,@Id

END
